hh3cEOCCommon.name: hh3cEOCCommon
hh3cEOCCommon.contactinfo: SMB EOC Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. 310 Liuhe Road, Zhijiang Science Park, Hangzhou, P.R.China http://www.h3c.com Zip:310053.
hh3cEOCCommon.description: The objects in this MIB module are used to manage and display common configuration between Ethernet Passive Optical Network (EOC) port which are based on the Ethernet in the First Mile (EFM) Passive Optical Network(PON) as defined in IEEE Draft P802.3ah/D3.0 clause 60, 64, 65.. and Ethernet Over Cable (EOC) which is based on HomePlug AV Specification.

hh3cEOCCommonSysVersion.name: hh3cEOCCommonSysVersion
hh3cEOCCommonSysVersion.description: Eoc version. If the object length is zero, it means the version is unknown. The length is up to 1024.

hh3cEOCCommonUpLinkMacAddress.name: hh3cEOCCommonUpLinkMacAddress
hh3cEOCCommonUpLinkMacAddress.description: EOC CLT's uplink device's mac address.

hh3cEOCCommonCltManTable.name: hh3cEOCCommonCltManTable
hh3cEOCCommonCltManTable.description: This table defines the primary parameters of the CLT configuration.

hh3cEOCCommonCltManEntry.name: hh3cEOCCommonCltManEntry
hh3cEOCCommonCltManEntry.description: The entry of the table hh3cEOCCommonCltManTable.

hh3cEOCCommonCltAutoAuthorize.name: hh3cEOCCommonCltAutoAuthorize
hh3cEOCCommonCltAutoAuthorize.description: This value determines whether software performs self-authorization for each Cable Network Unit(CNU) registering to the network. Setting it to false means for every CNU registering, software requires external authorization, and until it's done the CNU is not authenticated. True value means software authorizes each CNU registering to the network automatically.

hh3cEOCCommonCltMaxAllowToAccess.name: hh3cEOCCommonCltMaxAllowToAccess
hh3cEOCCommonCltMaxAllowToAccess.description: This value determines how many CNU can be bound in this CLT. If the number of CNU is more than this value , then the rest of CNU should not be allow to access.

hh3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMinVal.name: hh3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMinVal
hh3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMinVal.description: The lower limit of total-bandwidth which is confined to hh3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBW.

hh3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMaxVal.name: hh3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMaxVal
hh3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMaxVal.description: The upper limit of total-bandwidth which is confined to hh3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBW.

hh3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMinVal.name: hh3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMinVal
hh3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMinVal.description: The lower limit of high priority bandwidth which is confined to hh3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW.

hh3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMaxVal.name: hh3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMaxVal
hh3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMaxVal.description: The upper limit of high priority bandwidth which is confined to hh3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW.

hh3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMinVal.name: hh3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMinVal
hh3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMinVal.description: The lower limit of total-bandwidth which is confined to hh3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBW.

hh3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMaxVal.name: hh3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMaxVal
hh3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMaxVal.description: The upper limit of total-bandwidth which is confined to hh3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBW.

hh3cEOCComCnuAttenThrA.name: hh3cEOCComCnuAttenThrA
hh3cEOCComCnuAttenThrA.description: The value of cnu's average attenuation good level thresholds.

hh3cEOCComCnuAttenThrB.name: hh3cEOCComCnuAttenThrB
hh3cEOCComCnuAttenThrB.description: The value of cnu's average attenuation normal level thresholds.

hh3cEOCComCnuRateDropThr.name: hh3cEOCComCnuRateDropThr
hh3cEOCComCnuRateDropThr.description: The value of cnu's Tx/Rx rate drop thresholds.

hh3cEOCComCnuSysManTable.name: hh3cEOCComCnuSysManTable
hh3cEOCComCnuSysManTable.description: This table implements the management of CNUs(Coax Network Unit).

hh3cEOCComCnuSysManEntry.name: hh3cEOCComCnuSysManEntry
hh3cEOCComCnuSysManEntry.description: The entry of the table hh3cEOCComCnuSysManTable.

hh3cEOCComCnuCableIfindex.name: hh3cEOCComCnuCableIfindex
hh3cEOCComCnuCableIfindex.description: The index of cable port which uniquely identifies the cable port of one device.

hh3cEOCComCnuDeviceType.name: hh3cEOCComCnuDeviceType
hh3cEOCComCnuDeviceType.description: The type of the EOC CNU(Coax Network Unit).

hh3cEOCComCnuDeviceAlias.name: hh3cEOCComCnuDeviceAlias
hh3cEOCComCnuDeviceAlias.description: EOC CNU's alias which display as the device's name, it's recommended to set it uniquely and understandably.

hh3cEOCComCnuDescr.name: hh3cEOCComCnuDescr
hh3cEOCComCnuDescr.description: User's description, including user's address, name, telephone number and so on.

hh3cEOCComCnuUpTime.name: hh3cEOCComCnuUpTime
hh3cEOCComCnuUpTime.description: The time since the CNU last registered to the network.

hh3cEOCComCnuVLANType.name: hh3cEOCComCnuVLANType
hh3cEOCComCnuVLANType.description: port vlan types. hybrid (3) port can carry multiple VLANs. If fabric function is supported, fabric(4) means the port is a fabric port.

hh3cEOCComCnuPvid.name: hh3cEOCComCnuPvid
hh3cEOCComCnuPvid.description: The PVID, the VLAN ID assigned to untagged frames or Priority-Tagged frames received on cable interface.

hh3cEOCComCnuVlanTag.name: hh3cEOCComCnuVlanTag
hh3cEOCComCnuVlanTag.description: VLAN is set tagged or untagged on cable interface.

hh3cEOCComCnuReset.name: hh3cEOCComCnuReset
hh3cEOCComCnuReset.description: This variable is used to reset the CNU device. The interface may be unavailable while the reset occurs and data may be lost. During reading operation it returns the state of the CNU device. running(1) indicates and operates normal operation, reset(2) indicates and operates reset mode. Writing can be done all the time.

hh3cEOCComCnuSave.name: hh3cEOCComCnuSave
hh3cEOCComCnuSave.description: Save the UNI and CNU related configurations to the CNU.

hh3cEOCComCnuAccess.name: hh3cEOCComCnuAccess
hh3cEOCComCnuAccess.description: Control whether the user can access to the network.

hh3cEOCComCnuMacTable.name: hh3cEOCComCnuMacTable
hh3cEOCComCnuMacTable.description: This table implements the management of CNUs.

hh3cEOCComCnuMacEntry.name: hh3cEOCComCnuMacEntry
hh3cEOCComCnuMacEntry.description: The entry of the table hh3cEOCComCnuMacTable.

hh3cEOCComCnuTempIndex.name: hh3cEOCComCnuTempIndex
hh3cEOCComCnuTempIndex.description: EOC CNU's model index from hh3cHPEOCTemplateIndex, If configure 0, the CNU select no model.

hh3cEOCComCnuInfoTable.name: hh3cEOCComCnuInfoTable
hh3cEOCComCnuInfoTable.description: Primary status of the specified CNU. There will be one row in this table for each information in the system.

hh3cEOCComCnuHardwareVersion.name: hh3cEOCComCnuHardwareVersion
hh3cEOCComCnuHardwareVersion.description: EOC CNU's hardware version. If the object length is zero, it means the version is unknown.

hh3cEOCComCnuLinkState.name: hh3cEOCComCnuLinkState
hh3cEOCComCnuLinkState.description: The cable port's link state. The physicaldown(1) state indicates that the CNU is not powered on. The linkdown(2) state indicates that the CNU is powered on, but registers fail. The linkup(3) state indicates that the CNU is powered on, and registers successful. The loopback(4) state indecates that the CNU is powered on and registers successful, but loopback has detected.

hh3cEOCComCnuSoftwareVersion.name: hh3cEOCComCnuSoftwareVersion
hh3cEOCComCnuSoftwareVersion.description: EOC CNU's software version. If the object length is zero, it means the version is unknown.

hh3cEOCComCnuTxRate.name: hh3cEOCComCnuTxRate
hh3cEOCComCnuTxRate.description: The cnu's capability of tx speed in unit of 1Mbps.

hh3cEOCComCnuRxRate.name: hh3cEOCComCnuRxRate
hh3cEOCComCnuRxRate.description: The cnu's capability of rx speed in unit of 1Mbps.

hh3cEOCComCnuTxRateDrop.name: hh3cEOCComCnuTxRateDrop
hh3cEOCComCnuTxRateDrop.description: The cnu's capability droping of tx speed from it's history max value in unit of %.

hh3cEOCComCnuRxRateDrop.name: hh3cEOCComCnuRxRateDrop
hh3cEOCComCnuRxRateDrop.description: The cnu's capability droping of rx speed from it's history max value in unit of %.

hh3cEOCComCnuBandWidthEntry.name: hh3cEOCComCnuBandWidthEntry
hh3cEOCComCnuBandWidthEntry.description: The entry of table hh3cEOCComCnuBandWidthTable. It is a pre-configuration.

hh3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBW.name: hh3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBW
hh3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBW.description: Maximum bandwidth allowed for the CNU, measured in Kbit/s.

hh3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW.name: hh3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW
hh3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW.description: High priority bandwidth - measured in Kbit/s. The value of this object should be the multiple of the value of hh3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBW. The high priority bandwidth should not be larger than the maximum bandwidth.

hh3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBW.name: hh3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBW
hh3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBW.description: Total bandwidth - measured in Kbit/s. The value of this object should be the multiple of the value of hh3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW. The total bandwidth should be larger than the high priority bandwidth.

hh3cEOCComUniManTable.name: hh3cEOCComUniManTable
hh3cEOCComUniManTable.description: This table defines several user network interface(UNI) system parameters.

hh3cEOCUniIndex.name: hh3cEOCUniIndex
hh3cEOCUniIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the FE(Fast Ethernet) interface of the CNU.

hh3cEOCComUniDescr.name: hh3cEOCComUniDescr
hh3cEOCComUniDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the interface. This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the interface hardware and software.

hh3cEOCComUniStatus.name: hh3cEOCComUniStatus
hh3cEOCComUniStatus.description: The desired state of the user network interface. When a managed system initializes, all user network interfaces start with down state. The testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed. As a result of either explicit management action or per configuration information retained by the managed system, hh3cEOCComUniStatus is then changed to either the up or testing states (or remains in the down state).

hh3cEOCComUniCurrentSpeed.name: hh3cEOCComUniCurrentSpeed
hh3cEOCComUniCurrentSpeed.description: An estimate of the interface's current bandwidth in bits per second. For interfaces which do not vary in bandwidth or for those where no accurate estimation can be made, this object should contain the nominal bandwidth. If the bandwidth of the interface is greater than the maximum value reportable by this object then this object should report its maximum value (4,294,967,295). For a sub-layer which has no concept of bandwidth, this object should be zero.

hh3cEOCComUniCurrentDuplex.name: hh3cEOCComUniCurrentDuplex
hh3cEOCComUniCurrentDuplex.description: The current mode of operation of the MAC entity. 'unknown' indicates that the current duplex mode could not be determined. Management control of the duplex mode is accomplished through the MAU MIB. When an interface does not support autonegotiation, or when autonegotiation is not enabled, the duplex mode is controlled using ifMauDefaultType. When autonegotiation is supported and enabled, duplex mode is controlled using ifMauAutoNegAdvertisedBits. In either case, the currently operating duplex mode is reflected both in this object and in ifMauType. Note that this object provides redundant information with ifMauType. Normally, redundant objects are discouraged. However, in this instance, it allows a management application to determine the duplex status of an interface without having to know every possible value of ifMauType. This was felt to be sufficiently valuable to justify the redundancy.

hh3cEOCComUniMdi.name: hh3cEOCComUniMdi
hh3cEOCComUniMdi.description: Type of the line connected to UNI interface: mdi-ii(straight-through cable), mdi-x (crossover cable), mdi-auto (auto-sensing).

hh3cEOCComUniFlowControl.name: hh3cEOCComUniFlowControl
hh3cEOCComUniFlowControl.description: Flow control status. true(1) - Flow control status enable. false(2) - Flow control status disable.

hh3cEOCComUniCountReset.name: hh3cEOCComUniCountReset
hh3cEOCComUniCountReset.description: Reset the counter which is about packets of the interface, then the counter will change to zero. There is no sense in reading this object.

hh3cEOCComUniAlias.name: hh3cEOCComUniAlias
hh3cEOCComUniAlias.description: This object is an 'alias' name for the interface as specified by a network manager, and provides a non- volatile 'handle' for the interface. On the first instantiation of an interface, the value of hh3cEOCComUniAlias associated with that interface is the zero-length string. As and when a value is written into an instance of hh3cEOCComUniAlias through a network management set operation, then the agent must retain the supplied value in the hh3cEOCComUniAlias instance associated with the same interface for as long as that interface remains instantiated, including across all re- initializations/reboots of the network management system, including those which result in a change of the interface's ifIndex and hh3cEOCUniIndex value. An example of the value which a network manager might store in this object for a WAN interface is the (Telco's) circuit number/identifier of the interface. Some agents may support write-access only for interfaces having particular values of hh3cEOCComUniType. An agent which supports write access to this object is required to keep the value in non-volatile storage, but it may limit the length of new values depending on how much storage is already occupied by the current values for other interfaces.

hh3cEOCComUniType.name: hh3cEOCComUniType
hh3cEOCComUniType.description: The type of interface. Additional values for hh3cEOCComUniType are assigned by the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority(IANA), through updating the syntax of the IANAifType textual convention.

hh3cEOCComUniVLANType.name: hh3cEOCComUniVLANType
hh3cEOCComUniVLANType.description: port vlan types. hybrid (3) port can carry multiple VLANs. If fabric function is supported, fabric(4) means the port is a fabric port.

hh3cEOCComUniPvid.name: hh3cEOCComUniPvid
hh3cEOCComUniPvid.description: The PVID, the VLAN ID assigned to untagged frames or Priority-Tagged frames received on this port.

hh3cEOCComUniVlanTag.name: hh3cEOCComUniVlanTag
hh3cEOCComUniVlanTag.description: VLAN is set tagged or untagged.

hh3cEOCComUniPriority.name: hh3cEOCComUniPriority
hh3cEOCComUniPriority.description: The default ingress User Priority for this port. This only has effect on media, such as Ethernet, that do not support native User Priority.

hh3cEOCComUniUpLineRate.name: hh3cEOCComUniUpLineRate
hh3cEOCComUniUpLineRate.description: The max speed upload in units of 1,000 bits per second on this interface. The value should between 0 and 100Mbps. If the value is 0, it means that the upload speed is only restricted by the physical line.

hh3cEOCComUniDownLineRate.name: hh3cEOCComUniDownLineRate
hh3cEOCComUniDownLineRate.description: The max speed download in units of 1,000 bits per second on this interface. The value should between 0 and 100Mbps. If the value is 0, it means that the download speed is only restricted by the physical line.

hh3cEOCComUniAdminStatus.name: hh3cEOCComUniAdminStatus
hh3cEOCComUniAdminStatus.description: Control if open or close the UNI. If choose up(1), means the UNI is opened and packets can pass it. If choose down(2), means the UNI is closed and all packets will be discard.

hh3cEOCComUniCountTable.name: hh3cEOCComUniCountTable
hh3cEOCComUniCountTable.description: A list of interface counter about frames entries.

hh3cEOCComUniCountEntry.name: hh3cEOCComUniCountEntry
hh3cEOCComUniCountEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular interface.

hh3cEOCUniInPkts.name: hh3cEOCUniInPkts
hh3cEOCUniInPkts.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets, broadcast packets, and multicast packets) received.

hh3cEOCUniInUPkts.name: hh3cEOCUniInUPkts
hh3cEOCUniInUPkts.description: The total number of good packets received that are directed to the unicast address. Note that this does not include multicast and broadcast packets.

hh3cEOCUniInBPkts.name: hh3cEOCUniInBPkts
hh3cEOCUniInBPkts.description: The total number of good packets received that are directed to the broadcast address. Note that this does not include multicast packets.

hh3cEOCUniInMPkts.name: hh3cEOCUniInMPkts
hh3cEOCUniInMPkts.description: The total number of good packets received that are directed to a multicast address. Note that this number does not include packets directed to the broadcast address.

hh3cEOCUniInPausePkts.name: hh3cEOCUniInPausePkts
hh3cEOCUniInPausePkts.description: A count of MAC Control packets received on this interface by the pause(flow control) operation. This counter does not increment when the interface is in a half-duplex mode. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system.

hh3cEOCUniInTotalErrors.name: hh3cEOCUniInTotalErrors
hh3cEOCUniInTotalErrors.description: Total count of the error packets received on this interface.

hh3cEOCUniInCRCErrs.name: hh3cEOCUniInCRCErrs
hh3cEOCUniInCRCErrs.description: The total number of packets received that had a length (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) of between 64 and 1518 octets, inclusive, but had either a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS) with an integral number of octets (FCS Error) or a bad FCS with a non-integral number of octets (Alignment Error).

hh3cEOCUniInUndersizePkts.name: hh3cEOCUniInUndersizePkts
hh3cEOCUniInUndersizePkts.description: The total number of packets received that are less than 64 octets long (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and are otherwise well formed.

hh3cEOCUniInOversizePkts.name: hh3cEOCUniInOversizePkts
hh3cEOCUniInOversizePkts.description: The total number of packets received that are longer than 1518 octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and are otherwise well formed.

hh3cEOCUniInErrorbyOther.name: hh3cEOCUniInErrorbyOther
hh3cEOCUniInErrorbyOther.description: The total number of other error packets received on this interface.

hh3cEOCUniInOctets.name: hh3cEOCUniInOctets
hh3cEOCUniInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on this interface.

hh3cEOCUniOutPkts.name: hh3cEOCUniOutPkts
hh3cEOCUniOutPkts.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets, broadcast packets, and multicast packets) sent.

hh3cEOCUniOutUPkts.name: hh3cEOCUniOutUPkts
hh3cEOCUniOutUPkts.description: The total number of good packets sent that are directed to the unicast address. Note that this does not include multicast and broadcast packets.

hh3cEOCUniOutBPkts.name: hh3cEOCUniOutBPkts
hh3cEOCUniOutBPkts.description: The total number of good packets sent that are directed to the broadcast address. Note that this does not include multicast packets.

hh3cEOCUniOutMPkts.name: hh3cEOCUniOutMPkts
hh3cEOCUniOutMPkts.description: The total number of good packets sent that are directed to a multicast address. Note that this number does not include packets directed to the broadcast address.

hh3cEOCUniOutPausePkts.name: hh3cEOCUniOutPausePkts
hh3cEOCUniOutPausePkts.description: The total number of MAC control packets sent on this interface by the pause operation. This counter does not increment when the interface is in a half-duplex mode. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system.

hh3cEOCUniOutTotalErrors.name: hh3cEOCUniOutTotalErrors
hh3cEOCUniOutTotalErrors.description: The total number of error packets sent on this interface.

hh3cEOCUniOutCollisions.name: hh3cEOCUniOutCollisions
hh3cEOCUniOutCollisions.description: The best estimate of the total number of collisions on this Ethernet segment. The value returned will depend on the location of the RMON probe. Section 8.2.1.3 (10BASE-5) and section 10.3.1.3 (10BASE-2) of IEEE standard 802.3 states that a station must detect a collision, in the receive mode, if three or more stations are transmitting simultaneously. A repeater port must detect a collision when two or more stations are transmitting simultaneously. Thus a probe placed on a repeater port could record more collisions than a probe connected to a station on the same segment could. Probe location plays a much smaller role when considering 10BASE-T. 14.2.1.4 (10BASE-T) of IEEE standard 802.3 defines a collision as the simultaneous presence of signals on the DO and RD circuits (transmitting and receiving at the same time). A 10BASE-T station can only detect collisions when it is transmitting. Thus probes placed on a station and a repeater, should report the same number of collisions. Note also that an RMON probe inside a repeater should ideally report collisions between the repeater and one or more other hosts (transmit collisions as defined by IEEE 802.3k) plus receiver collisions observed on any coax segments to which the repeater is connected.

hh3cEOCUniOutDelayExceedDsds.name: hh3cEOCUniOutDelayExceedDsds
hh3cEOCUniOutDelayExceedDsds.description: The number of packets discarded by this port due to excessive transit delay through the bridge. It is incremented by both transparent and source route bridges.

hh3cEOCUniOutErrorbyOther.name: hh3cEOCUniOutErrorbyOther
hh3cEOCUniOutErrorbyOther.description: The total number of other error packets sent on this interface. Other error packets means the error packets out of collision packets and excessive delayed packets.

hh3cEOCUniOutDroppedFrames.name: hh3cEOCUniOutDroppedFrames
hh3cEOCUniOutDroppedFrames.description: The total number of frames dropped because of buffer failure.

hh3cEOCUniOutOctets.name: hh3cEOCUniOutOctets
hh3cEOCUniOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface.

hh3cEOCCnuRegExcessTrap.name: hh3cEOCCnuRegExcessTrap
hh3cEOCCnuRegExcessTrap.description: A hh3cEOCCnuRegExcessTrap notification is sent when the number of registered CNUs exceeds the limit.

hh3cEOCCnuRegExcessRecoverTrap.name: hh3cEOCCnuRegExcessRecoverTrap
hh3cEOCCnuRegExcessRecoverTrap.description: A hh3cEOCCnuRegExcessRecoverTrap notification is sent when hh3cEOCCnuRegExcessTrap is detected and then recoverd.

hh3cEOCCnuRegSuccTrap.name: hh3cEOCCnuRegSuccTrap
hh3cEOCCnuRegSuccTrap.description: A hh3cEOCCnuRegSuccTrap notification is sent when a CNU registers successful.

hh3cEOCCnuOffLineTrap.name: hh3cEOCCnuOffLineTrap
hh3cEOCCnuOffLineTrap.description: A hh3cEOCCnuOffLineTrap notification is sent when a CNU offline.

hh3cEOCCnuLinkupTrap.name: hh3cEOCCnuLinkupTrap
hh3cEOCCnuLinkupTrap.description: A hh3cEOCCnuLinkupTrap notification is sent when a CNU linkup.

hh3cEOCOamDisconnectTrap.name: hh3cEOCOamDisconnectTrap
hh3cEOCOamDisconnectTrap.description: A hh3cEOCOamDisconnectionTrap notification is sent when LLID's OAM link is disconnected.

hh3cEOCOamDisconnectRecoverTrap.name: hh3cEOCOamDisconnectRecoverTrap
hh3cEOCOamDisconnectRecoverTrap.description: A hh3cEOCOamDisconnectionRecoverTrap notification is sent when LLID's OAM link is disconnected and then connected.

hh3cEOCBandwidthNotEnoughTrap.name: hh3cEOCBandwidthNotEnoughTrap
hh3cEOCBandwidthNotEnoughTrap.description: Bandwidth is not enough, cnu can not bind now.

hh3cEOCCnuAttenuationTrap.name: hh3cEOCCnuAttenuationTrap
hh3cEOCCnuAttenuationTrap.description: A hh3cHPEOCCnuAttenuationTrap notification is sent when a CNU's attenuation is changing.

hh3cEOCCnuRegFailTrap.name: hh3cEOCCnuRegFailTrap
hh3cEOCCnuRegFailTrap.description: A hh3cEOCCnuRegFailTrap notification is sent when a CNU registers fail.

hh3cEOCCLTCablePortErrorTrap.name: hh3cEOCCLTCablePortErrorTrap
hh3cEOCCLTCablePortErrorTrap.description: A hh3cEOCCLTCablePortErrorTrap notification is sent when the hardware of cable port occurs error or CLT's vlan is configged error.

hh3cEOCCLTCablePortErrReTrap.name: hh3cEOCCLTCablePortErrReTrap
hh3cEOCCLTCablePortErrReTrap.description: A hh3cEOCCLTCablePortErrReTrap notification is sent when cable port error and then recovered.

hh3cEOCCnuTxRateDropTrap.name: hh3cEOCCnuTxRateDropTrap
hh3cEOCCnuTxRateDropTrap.description: A hh3cEOCCnuTxRateDropTrap notification is sent when cable port rate of TX capability drop exceeded threshold.

hh3cEOCCnuTxRateDropRecoverTrap.name: hh3cEOCCnuTxRateDropRecoverTrap
hh3cEOCCnuTxRateDropRecoverTrap.description: A hh3cEOCCnuTxRateDropRecoverTrap notification is sent when cable port rate of TX capability recover from the recent rate-drop trap.

hh3cEOCCnuRxRateDropTrap.name: hh3cEOCCnuRxRateDropTrap
hh3cEOCCnuRxRateDropTrap.description: A hh3cEOCCnuRxRateDropTrap notification is sent when cable port rate of RX capability drop exceeded threshold.

hh3cEOCCnuRxRateDropRecoverTrap.name: hh3cEOCCnuRxRateDropRecoverTrap
hh3cEOCCnuRxRateDropRecoverTrap.description: A hh3cEOCCnuRxRateDropRecoverTrap notification is sent when cable port rate of RX capability recover from the recent rate-drop trap.
